    <exercisegroup permid="JKL">
      <title>Plotting Points and Choosing a Scale</title>
      <exercise permid="WIX">
        <webwork>
            <statement>
              <p permid="hwx">
                What would be the difficulty with trying to plot <m>(12,4)</m>,
                <m>(13,5)</m>, and <m>(310,208)</m> all on the same graph?
              </p>

              <p permid="NDG">
                <var form="essay" />
              </p>
            </statement>
            <solution permid="NZf">
              <p permid="POs">
                Answers will vary,
                but the issue is that once you set the scale on both axes so that both <m>(12,4)</m> and <m>(310,208)</m> will appear,
                then <m>(13,5)</m> will appear to be so close to <m>(12,4)</m> that it will be challenging to draw them both and make it clear they are two different points.
              </p>
            </solution>
